### 1. CREATE New Todo (POST)
# @name createTodo
POST http://localhost:8080/api/todos
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "title": "Finish Spring Boot project",
    "description": "Complete the in-memory Todo API",
    "completed": false
}

### 2. CREATE Another Todo (POST) - to ensure we have multiple items
# @name createAnother
POST http://localhost:8080/api/todos
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "title": "Buy coffee filters",
    "description": "Check supply before Friday",
    "completed": false
}

### 3. READ ALL Todos (GET)
# This should return an array containing items created in steps 1 and 2.
GET http://localhost:8080/api/todos

### 4. READ Todo by ID (GET)
# Assuming the first item created has ID 1
GET http://localhost:8080/api/todos/1

### 5. UPDATE an Existing Todo (PUT)
# We will mark the first item (ID 1) as completed
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/todos/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "title": "Finish Spring Boot project - COMPLETED",
    "description": "Complete the in-memory Todo API",
    "completed": true 
}

### 6. READ ALL to Verify Update (GET)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/todos

### 7. DELETE a Todo (DELETE)
# Delete the second item (ID 2)
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/todos/2